# Videos are far too large for GitHub (100 MB file limit).
# Host course videos on Google Drive or YouTube and paste the link
# into the course builder instead.
video/

# Only the lowercase-named images below are used by the site.
# The original mixed-case exports stay local to keep the repo lean.
images/*
!images/logo-globe.png
!images/org-chart.png
!images/bbb.jpg
!images/google-2.png
!images/ramsey.jpg
!images/max-about-us-2.jpg

# Knowledge Check answer keys contain correct answers — this repo is
# public (GitHub Pages requires a paid plan to publish from a private
# repo), so these stay local-only. Claude reads them locally and
# uploads the answers straight into the Google Sheet backend; they
# never reach GitHub. The TEMPLATE copy is a harmless empty
# placeholder and stays tracked as a reference for the file format.
Courses/*/knowledge-check.js
!Courses/TEMPLATE/knowledge-check.js

# Local dev tooling (not part of the site)
.claude/

# OS noise
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.DS_Store
